has post format "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
===============================================================

NAME
----

has post format - Returns a boolean if the specified [post

SYNOPSIS
--------

Returns a boolean if the specified [post
format](/Post_Formats "Post Formats") is assigned (true) or not (false)
to the post. This will usually be called in the [the
loop](/The_Loop "The Loop"), but can be used anywhere if a post ID is
provided.

USAGE
-----

` <?php $format = has_post_format($format,$post_id); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$format` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*Required*) name of the post format.
    Default: none

 `$post_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*Optional*) ID of the post.
    Default: current loop post

CHANGELOG
---------

-   Since: [3.1](/Version_3.1 "Version 3.1")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`has_post_format()` is located in `wp-includes/post.php`.

[**Post Formats**](/Post_Formats "Post Formats"):
[set\_post\_format()](/Function_Reference/set_post_format "Function Reference/set post format"),
[get\_post\_format()](/Function_Reference/get_post_format "Function Reference/get post format"),
**has\_post\_format()**

